(87, 1, '2024-12-17 12:10:57', '2024-12-17 12:10:57', 'The Arduino Uno R3 is one of the most popular and widely used microcontroller boards in the Arduino family. Based on the ATmega328P microcontroller, it is a versatile and easy-to-use platform that is perfect for beginners and advanced users alike. The Uno R3 is ideal for a wide range of projects, from simple LED blink programs to complex robotics and sensor networks. With 14 digital I/O pins, 6 analog inputs, and a USB interface, it offers sufficient connectivity for most basic and intermediate applications. It is fully compatible with the Arduino IDE, making it easy to program and integrate with various sensors and modules.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nMicrocontroller: ATmega328P with 32 KB of flash memory, 2 KB SRAM, and 1 KB EEPROM.\r\nDigital I/O Pins: 14 digital input/output pins, 6 of which can be used as PWM outputs.\r\nAnalog Inputs: 6 analog inputs for connecting sensors and other analog devices.\r\nUSB Interface: USB-B connector for programming and serial communication with your computer.\r\nOperating Voltage: 5V, making it compatible with most sensors, actuators, and modules.\r\nPower Supply: Powered via USB or an external 7-12V DC power supply.\r\nCommunication: Supports serial communication via USB and with external devices using software serial.\r\nApplications: Robotics, home automation, sensor projects, LED control, motor control, and much more.\r\n\r\nThe Arduino Uno R3 is the go-to board for beginners due to its simplicity and wide community support. It\'s perfect for anyone starting with electronics and programming, as well as for prototyping various applications.', 'Arduino Uno R3', 'A popular microcontroller board based on the ATmega328P.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'arduino-uno-r3', '', '', '2024-12-19 19:22:11', '2024-12-19 19:22:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=87', 0, 'product', '', 0),
