(93, 1, '2024-12-17 12:21:47', '2024-12-17 12:21:47', 'The DHT11 is a popular temperature and humidity sensor used in various Arduino-based projects to monitor environmental conditions. It provides both temperature and humidity readings, making it ideal for applications such as weather stations, climate control systems, and home automation. The sensor uses a single digital signal to transmit the data, simplifying the interface with Arduino boards. Although less precise than other sensors, the DHT11 is cost-effective and easy to use, making it a great choice for basic environmental monitoring projects.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nTemperature Range: Measures temperature from 0°C to 50°C (32°F to 122°F) with an accuracy of ±2°C.\r\nHumidity Range: Measures humidity from 20% to 80% RH (Relative Humidity) with an accuracy of ±5% RH.\r\nOperating Voltage: Typically operates at 3.3V to 5V, compatible with most Arduino boards.\r\nDigital Output: Outputs data in a digital format, which simplifies connection and data retrieval.\r\nLow Power Consumption: Efficient and ideal for battery-operated projects.\r\nSimple Interface: Uses a single data pin for communication, reducing wiring complexity.\r\nApplications: Weather stations, climate control systems, greenhouses, smart home devices, and more.\r\n\r\nThe DHT11 sensor is a great entry-level component for those looking to measure temperature and humidity in Arduino projects, offering a balance between affordability, ease of use, and adequate accuracy for general applications.', 'DHT11 Temperature and Humidity Sensor', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'dht11-temperature-and-humidity-sensor', '', '', '2024-12-19 19:21:25', '2024-12-19 19:21:25', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=93', 0, 'product', '', 0),
(94, 1, '2024-12-17 12:21:02', '2024-12-17 12:21:02', '', 'DHT11 Temperature and Humidity Sensor', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'dht11-temperature-and-humidity-sensor', '', '', '2024-12-17 12:21:02', '2024-12-17 12:21:02', '', 93, 'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/DHT11-Temperature-and-Humidity-Sensor.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(95, 1, '2024-12-17 12:23:13', '2024-12-17 12:23:13', 'The ultrasonic distance sensor is a commonly used component in Arduino projects to measure the distance to an object using sound waves. The sensor emits ultrasonic waves, which bounce off objects and return to the sensor. By measuring the time it takes for the waves to return, the sensor can calculate the distance to the object. This makes it ideal for applications such as obstacle avoidance in robots, distance measurement, and rangefinding. The ultrasonic sensor is easy to integrate with Arduino boards and provides accurate distance measurements with minimal power consumption.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nDistance Range: Typically measures distances from 2 cm to 4 meters, with some models supporting even greater ranges.\r\nOperating Voltage: Usually operates at 5V, making it compatible with most Arduino boards.\r\nAccuracy: Provides high accuracy with a typical margin of error around 1 cm, making it suitable for precise distance measurement.\r\nSimple Interface: Uses two pins (Trig and Echo) for communication with Arduino, with a straightforward pulse measurement technique.\r\nPower Efficiency: Consumes low power, ideal for battery-powered projects.\r\nMeasuring Units: Measures distance in centimeters or inches, depending on configuration.\r\nApplications: Robotics (for obstacle avoidance), parking sensors, water level detection, distance-based measurements in home automation, and more.\r\n\r\nThe ultrasonic distance sensor is a versatile, easy-to-use component that provides precise and reliable distance measurements in a variety of Arduino projects.', 'Ultrasonic Distance Sensor', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ultrasonic-distance-sensor', '', '', '2024-12-19 19:19:28', '2024-12-19 19:19:28', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=95', 0, 'product', '', 0),
(96, 1, '2024-12-17 12:22:47', '2024-12-17 12:22:47', '', 'Ultrasonic Distance Sensor', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'ultrasonic-distance-sensor', '', '', '2024-12-17 12:22:47', '2024-12-17 12:22:47', '', 95, 'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Ultrasonic-Distance-Sensor.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(97, 1, '2024-12-17 12:26:18', '2024-12-17 12:26:18', 'A servo motor is a type of motor that allows precise control of angular position. Unlike a regular DC motor that rotates continuously, a servo motor can rotate to a specific angle within a certain range (typically 0° to 180°). This makes servo motors ideal for applications requiring accurate and controlled motion, such as in robotics, mechanical arms, camera sliders, and steering mechanisms. Servo motors are controlled using PWM (Pulse Width Modulation) signals, which makes them easy to integrate with Arduino boards for precise positioning.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nPrecise Control: Offers precise positioning, typically with a range of 180° or more, depending on the model.\r\nOperating Voltage: Typically operates at 4.8V to 6V, making it compatible with many Arduino boards.\r\nTorque: Provides high torque at low speeds, allowing for the manipulation of objects or components with ease.\r\nEasy Control: Controlled using PWM signals from an Arduino, allowing you to set the desired angle and movement.\r\nCompact and Efficient: Small in size with low power consumption, ideal for space-constrained projects.\r\nApplications: Robotics, remote-controlled cars, automated doors, camera sliders, robotic arms, and more.\r\nFeedback System: Includes a built-in feedback mechanism that helps maintain the desired position.\r\n\r\nServo motors are a great solution for precise, controlled movement in Arduino-based projects, offering reliable performance for applications requiring accurate positioning and motio', 'Servo Motor', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'servo-motor', '', '', '2024-12-19 19:19:33', '2024-12-19 19:19:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=97', 0, 'product', '', 0),
(98, 1, '2024-12-17 12:25:32', '2024-12-17 12:25:32', '', 'Servo Motor', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'servo-motor', '', '', '2024-12-17 12:25:32', '2024-12-17 12:25:32', '', 97, 'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Servo-Motor.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(99, 1, '2024-12-17 12:28:01', '2024-12-17 12:28:01', 'A stepper motor is a type of DC motor that moves in discrete steps, offering precise control over its position, speed, and rotation direction. Unlike regular DC motors, which spin continuously when powered, stepper motors divide a full rotation into several equal steps, allowing for highly accurate movements. This makes stepper motors ideal for applications requiring precise control, such as 3D printers, CNC machines, robotics, and automated systems. With an Arduino, you can easily control the stepper motor\'s speed and position using simple programming and motor drivers.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nPrecise Control: Moves in fixed, equal steps, offering precise positioning and rotation control.\r\nHigh Torque: Provides high torque at low speeds, making it suitable for tasks requiring power and accuracy.\r\nOperating Voltage: Typically operates at 5V to 12V, making it compatible with many Arduino boards.\r\nCommon Types: Includes unipolar and bipolar stepper motors, with bipolar motors offering more torque and efficiency.\r\nStep Angles: Common step angles range from 1.8° to 0.9° per step, providing precise movement.\r\nDriver Compatibility: Works with motor driver ICs like the A4988 or DRV8825, allowing for easy control using Arduino\'s PWM signals.\r\nApplications: 3D printing, robotics, camera positioning, CNC machines, and automated systems.\r\nStepper motors, with their ability to provide precise and reliable control, are a key component for any project that requires accurate, controlled movements in robotics or automation.', 'Stepper Motor', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'stepper-motor', '', '', '2024-12-19 19:17:14', '2024-12-19 19:17:14', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=99', 0, 'product', '', 0),
