(103, 1, '2024-12-17 12:32:16', '2024-12-17 12:32:16', 'A breadboard is a versatile and essential tool for prototyping electronic circuits without the need for soldering. It allows you to build temporary circuits quickly and test components before creating a more permanent design. The breadboard is made of a grid of holes, which are electrically connected in rows and columns. Components such as resistors, capacitors, transistors, and microcontrollers like Arduino can be inserted into the holes, with connections made between the components using jumper wires. Breadboards are widely used by hobbyists, students, and engineers for experimenting with circuit designs and creating simple electronic projects.\r\n', 'Breadboard', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'breadboard', '', '', '2024-12-19 19:16:18', '2024-12-19 19:16:18', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=103', 0, 'product', '', 0),
