(105, 1, '2024-12-17 12:42:13', '2024-12-17 12:42:13', 'The Motor Shield for Arduino is a versatile and powerful accessory that allows you to control motors directly from an Arduino board. It provides a convenient way to drive DC motors, stepper motors, and servo motors without the need for complex wiring or additional motor driver circuits. By simply stacking the motor shield on top of an Arduino board, users can easily control the speed, direction, and position of motors in robotics, automation, and other motion-based projects. The motor shield simplifies the integration of motors into Arduino-based projects, making it a must-have for makers and hobbyists.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nMotor Types Supported: Can drive DC motors, stepper motors, and servo motors, offering flexibility for various applications.\r\nMotor Control: Provides independent control for each motor (speed and direction) using pulse-width modulation (PWM).\r\nPower Supply: Typically operates on a 5V or 12V power supply, depending on the motor requirements.\r\nCurrent Rating: Can supply up to 2A per motor, making it suitable for most small and medium motors.\r\nStackable Design: Easily connects to Arduino boards via the header pins, allowing other shields to be stacked for expanded functionality.\r\nOvercurrent Protection: Includes built-in protection to prevent damage from motor overcurrent situations.\r\nApplications: Robotics, automation systems, electric vehicles, home automation, and more.\r\n\r\nThe Motor Shield for Arduino is a reliable and efficient way to manage motor-based actions in your projects, providing essential control and safety features in a user-friendly package.', 'Motor Shield', 'Allows easy control of motors with Arduino boards.', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'motor-shield', '', '', '2024-12-19 19:14:38', '2024-12-19 19:14:38', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=105', 0, 'product', '', 0),
