(109, 1, '2024-12-17 12:46:04', '2024-12-17 12:46:04', 'The HC-05 Bluetooth module is a popular wireless communication component used in Arduino projects for enabling Bluetooth connectivity. It allows Arduino boards to communicate with other Bluetooth-enabled devices, such as smartphones, tablets, and computers. The module supports both master and slave modes, making it versatile for various communication needs. By connecting it to an Arduino, users can wirelessly control devices, send and receive data, or create remote control systems. The HC-05 module is commonly used in applications like remote-controlled cars, home automation, and wireless data transfer.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nBluetooth Version: Bluetooth 2.0 + EDR (Enhanced Data Rate), offering reliable communication over short to medium distances (typically up to 10 meters).\r\nOperating Voltage: 3.3V (logic level) and 5V (power supply), making it compatible with most Arduino boards.\r\nCommunication Protocol: Serial communication (UART), allowing easy integration with Arduino via TX/RX pins.\r\nModes: Can function as both master and slave for flexible connection options with other Bluetooth devices.\r\nTransmission Speed: Supports speeds of up to 3 Mbps for quick data transfer.\r\nLow Power Consumption: Ideal for battery-operated projects.\r\nApplications: Remote control systems, wireless sensor networks, data logging, and home automation.\r\n\r\nThe HC-05 Bluetooth module provides an easy and efficient way to add Bluetooth functionality to Arduino projects, enabling wireless communication and enhancing project interactivity.', 'Bluetooth Module (HC-05)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'bluetooth-module-hc-05', '', '', '2024-12-19 19:06:15', '2024-12-19 19:06:15', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=109', 0, 'product', '', 0),
