(191, 1, '2024-12-18 20:53:18', '2024-12-18 20:53:18', 'The 0.96-inch OLED display is a compact and high-quality screen often used in Arduino projects to display text, graphics, and data. This display utilizes organic light-emitting diode (OLED) technology, which offers high contrast and bright colors without requiring a backlight, making it more energy-efficient compared to traditional LCD displays. The 0.96-inch size is ideal for small projects where space is limited. It typically uses an I2C interface, allowing easy communication with Arduino boards using just two data pins, simplifying wiring and minimizing pin usage.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nDisplay Size: 0.96 inches, ideal for compact Arduino projects.\r\nResolution: 128x64 pixels, providing clear and sharp display of text and graphics.\r\nDisplay Type: OLED (Organic Light Emitting Diode), providing high contrast and bright colors with deep blacks.\r\nInterface: I2C communication (two data pins for easy connection).\r\nOperating Voltage: Typically 3.3V or 5V, compatible with most Arduino boards.\r\nLow Power Consumption: Does not require a backlight, making it energy-efficient.\r\nWide Viewing Angle: Offers excellent visibility from various angles.\r\nApplications: Displaying sensor data, time, status indicators, messages, and simple graphics in projects such as clocks, weather stations, and robotics.\r\n\r\nThe 0.96-inch OLED display is a popular choice for adding compact and clear visual output to Arduino projects, offering a simple and efficient solution for displaying a wide range of information.', 'OLED Display (0.96 inch)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'oled-display-0-96-inch', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:50:03', '2024-12-19 18:50:03', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=191', 0, 'product', '', 0),
