(193, 1, '2024-12-18 20:57:03', '2024-12-18 20:57:03', 'The MQ-2 gas sensor is a versatile and widely used sensor for detecting various gases such as methane, propane, alcohol, and smoke. It is commonly used in projects related to air quality monitoring, safety systems, and gas leak detection. The sensor works by detecting changes in the resistance of its heating element in the presence of specific gases, providing an analog output that can be read by an Arduino. The sensor\'s sensitivity can be adjusted by calibrating it with different gases, making it highly adaptable for different applications.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nOperating Voltage: Typically 5V, making it compatible with Arduino and other microcontrollers.\r\nDetection Gases: Methane (CH4), propane (C3H8), carbon monoxide (CO), smoke, alcohol, and more.\r\nSensitivity: Adjustable sensitivity, allowing fine-tuning for detecting specific gases.\r\nOutput Type: Analog output for continuous data and digital output for threshold detection.\r\nResponse Time: Quick response, typically within seconds after exposure to gases.\r\nApplications: Home safety systems, air quality monitoring, gas leak detection, environmental monitoring, and more.\r\nDurability: Reliable and long-lasting with proper calibration and maintenance.\r\n\r\nThe MQ-2 gas sensor is an affordable, easy-to-use component, perfect for building Arduino-based projects focused on detecting and monitoring gases in various environments.', 'Gas Sensor (MQ-2)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'gas-sensor-mq-2', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:48:31', '2024-12-19 18:48:31', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=193', 0, 'product', '', 0),
