(195, 1, '2024-12-18 20:59:27', '2024-12-18 20:59:27', 'A linear actuator is an electromechanical device used to create linear motion, ideal for applications requiring precise control over movement. In Arduino projects, linear actuators are commonly used for automating tasks like lifting, sliding, pushing, or pulling objects. The device converts rotational motion from a motor into straight-line motion via a screw or gear mechanism. It can be controlled using a motor driver or relay module connected to an Arduino board, enabling smooth and accurate motion control.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nOperating Voltage: Typically 12V or 24V DC, compatible with Arduino when paired with a motor driver.\r\nStroke Length: Available in various lengths (e.g., 50mm to 500mm), determining the range of motion.\r\nLoad Capacity: Can handle loads from a few kilograms to hundreds of kilograms, depending on the model.\r\nSpeed: Adjustable speed, usually ranging from 5mm/s to 50mm/s.\r\nDurability: Made of aluminum or steel, ensuring long-lasting performance in heavy-duty applications.\r\nFeedback Options: Some models include built-in limit switches or position sensors (potentiometer, Hall effect).\r\nApplications: Robotics, automation systems, adjustable furniture, door openers, solar panel tracking, etc.\r\n\r\nLinear actuators provide a reliable, precise, and versatile solution for adding motion control to Arduino projects, enabling the creation of smart and automated systems.', 'Linear Actuator', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'linear-actuator', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:41:55', '2024-12-19 18:41:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=195', 0, 'product', '', 0),
