(197, 1, '2024-12-18 21:04:23', '2024-12-18 21:04:23', 'A solenoid valve is an electronic component used to control the flow of liquids or gases in a system by opening or closing a passage. When integrated into Arduino projects, it allows for automated fluid management through electrical signals. The valve consists of a coil (electromagnet) that moves a piston or diaphragm to open or close the flow when powered.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nOperating Voltage: Commonly 12V or 24V DC, controlled via a relay or transistor connected to Arduino.\r\nMaterial: Made of plastic,steel, suitable for different fluid types (water, air, oil, etc.).\r\nOperation Type: Normally Closed (NC) – flow is blocked without power, or Normally Open (NO).\r\nPressure Range: Compatible with low to moderate pressures (e.g., 0-10 bar), depending on the model.\r\nFlow Rate: Determined by the inner diameter, typically 1/4\" to 1\".\r\nEase of Use: Connects easily to Arduino through control circuits like relays or MOSFETs.\r\nApplications: Automatic irrigation systems, fluid distribution, gas control, aquarium management, etc.\r\n\r\nSolenoid valves provide a reliable and precise solution for fluid control in Arduino projects. Their versatility and simplicity make them essential for creating automated systems involving liquids or gases.', 'Solenoid Valve', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'solenoid-valve', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:34:18', '2024-12-19 18:34:18', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=197', 0, 'product', '', 0),
