(201, 1, '2024-12-18 21:18:44', '2024-12-18 21:18:44', 'The piezo buzzer is an electronic component that converts electrical signals into sound. Easy to use with an Arduino board, it allows you to generate tones and sound alerts in various projects. This small device produces sound when an alternating current passes through its piezoelectric membrane. It can be controlled via a digital pin on the Arduino to create simple sounds, melodies, or alerts.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nOperating Voltage: Typically between 3 to 12V, compatible with Arduino outputs (5V).\r\nSound Type: Can produce continuous sounds or variable tones based on the input signal.\r\nEasy Integration: Connects to a digital pin and GND pin on the Arduino board.\r\nCompact and Lightweight: Ideal for projects requiring discreet components.\r\nLow Power Consumption: Energy-efficient, suitable for battery-powered projects.\r\nApplications: Alarms, sound indicators, melody generators, audio notifications in interactive projects.\r\nThe piezo buzzer is a popular choice for adding a sound dimension to Arduino projects, offering an affordable and simple solution to enhance user experience.', 'Piezo Buzzer', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'piezo-buzzer-module', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:31:18', '2024-12-19 18:31:18', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=201', 0, 'product', '', 0),
