(203, 1, '2024-12-18 21:22:45', '2024-12-18 21:22:45', 'The joystick module is a practical component used in Arduino projects to control movements or capture directional inputs. It is designed as an analog controller, similar to those found in video game controllers. The module features a lever that can be moved in two directions (X and Y axes) and includes a built-in push button activated by pressing the lever.\r\n\r\nKey Features:\r\nAnalog Axes: Provides two analog outputs (X and Y) to capture lever movements in two directions.\r\nPush Button: An integrated button activated by pressing the lever, connected via a digital output.\r\nOperating Voltage: Typically operates at 5V, compatible with Arduino microcontrollers.\r\nEasy Interface: Standard connectors (pins or headers) for quick integration.\r\nCompact and Lightweight: Ideal for portable or compact projects.\r\nApplications: Robot control, interactive games, camera management, etc.\r\nThis module is easy to use, durable, and perfect for adding an interactive interface to your Arduino projects. It offers a versatile combination of analog and digital control.', 'Joystick Module', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'joystick-module', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:29:29', '2024-12-19 18:29:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&#038;p=203', 0, 'product', '', 0),
