(205, 1, '2024-12-19 18:12:00', '2024-12-19 18:12:00', 'Le module joystick est un composant pratique utilisé dans des projets Arduino pour contrôler des mouvements ou capturer des entrées directionnelles. Il est conçu comme un contrôleur analogique, similaire à ceux trouvés dans les manettes de jeux vidéo. Le module comporte un levier qui peut être déplacé dans deux directions (axe X et Y) et est équipé d’un bouton-poussoir intégré activé en appuyant sur le levier.\n\nCaractéristiques principales :\nAxes analogiques : Fournit deux sorties analogiques (X et Y) pour capturer les déplacements du levier dans deux directions.\nBouton-poussoir : Un bouton intégré activé en appuyant sur le levier, connecté via une sortie numérique.\nTension de fonctionnement : Fonctionne généralement à 5V, compatible avec les microcontrôleurs Arduino.\nInterface facile : Connecteurs standard (broches ou headers) pour une intégration rapide.\nCompact et léger : Idéal pour des projets portables ou compacts.\nApplications : Contrôle de robots, jeux interactifs, gestion de caméras, etc.\nCe module est simple à utiliser, robuste, et parfait pour ajouter une interface interactive à vos projets Arduino, offrant une combinaison polyvalente de contrôle analogique et numérique.', 'Joystick Module', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '203-autosave-v1', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:12:00', '2024-12-19 18:12:00', '', 203, 'http://localhost/?p=205', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(206, 1, '2024-12-19 18:16:29', '2024-12-19 18:16:29', 'Used for sound and alarms.', 'Piezo Buzzer', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '201-autosave-v1', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:16:29', '2024-12-19 18:16:29', '', 201, 'http://localhost/?p=206', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(207, 1, '2024-12-19 18:26:07', '2024-12-19 18:26:07', 'Le câble USB pour Arduino permet de connecter une carte Arduino à un ordinateur pour l\'alimentation, le transfert de données et le téléversement de programmes. Compatible avec divers modèles d\'Arduino, il assure une connexion stable et rapide.\n\nCaractéristiques principales :\n\n-Types : USB-A vers USB-B ou micro-USB selon le modèle.\nLongueur : Généralement 1 à 2 mètres.\nCompatibilité : Compatible avec Arduino Uno, Mega, Nano, etc.\nMatériaux durables : Connecteurs robustes et câble flexible.', 'USB Cable for Arduino', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '199-autosave-v1', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:26:07', '2024-12-19 18:26:07', '', 199, 'http://localhost/?p=207', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(208, 1, '2024-12-19 18:33:24', '2024-12-19 18:33:24', 'A solenoid valve is an electronic component used to control the flow of liquids or gases in a system by opening or closing a passage. When integrated into Arduino projects, it allows for automated fluid management through electrical signals. The valve consists of a coil (electromagnet) that moves a piston or diaphragm to open or close the flow when powered.\n\nKey Features:\nOperating Voltage: Commonly 12V or 24V DC, controlled via a relay or transistor connected to Arduino.\nMaterial: Made of brass, plastic, or stainless steel, suitable for different fluid types (water, air, oil, etc.).\nOperation Type: Normally Closed (NC) – flow is blocked without power, or Normally Open (NO).\nPressure Range: Compatible with low to moderate pressures (e.g., 0-10 bar), depending on the model.\nFlow Rate: Determined by the inner diameter, typically 1/4\" to 1\".\nEase of Use: Connects easily to Arduino through control circuits like relays or MOSFETs.\nApplications: Automatic irrigation systems, fluid distribution, gas control, aquarium management, etc.\nSolenoid valves provide a reliable and precise solution for fluid control in Arduino projects. Their versatility and simplicity make them essential for creating automated systems involving liquids or gases.', 'Solenoid Valve', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '197-autosave-v1', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:33:24', '2024-12-19 18:33:24', '', 197, 'http://localhost/?p=208', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(209, 1, '2024-12-19 18:34:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 'AUTO-DRAFT', '', 'auto-draft', 'open', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:34:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?post_type=product&p=209', 0, 'product', '', 0),
(210, 1, '2024-12-19 18:38:10', '2024-12-19 18:38:10', 'A linear actuator is an electromechanical device used to create linear motion, ideal for applications requiring precise control over movement. In Arduino projects, linear actuators are commonly used for automating tasks like lifting, sliding, pushing, or pulling objects. The device converts rotational motion from a motor into straight-line motion via a screw or gear mechanism. It can be controlled using a motor driver or relay module connected to an Arduino board, enabling smooth and accurate motion control.\n\nKey Features:\nOperating Voltage: Typically 12V or 24V DC, compatible with Arduino when paired with a motor driver.\nStroke Length: Available in various lengths (e.g., 50mm to 500mm), determining the range of motion.\nLoad Capacity: Can handle loads from a few kilograms to hundreds of kilograms, depending on the model.\nSpeed: Adjustable speed, usually ranging from 5mm/s to 50mm/s.\nDurability: Made of aluminum or steel, ensuring long-lasting performance in heavy-duty applications.\nFeedback Options: Some models include built-in limit switches or position sensors (potentiometer, Hall effect).\nApplications: Robotics, automation systems, adjustable furniture, door openers, solar panel tracking, etc.\n\nLinear actuators provide a reliable, precise, and versatile solution for adding motion control to Arduino projects, enabling the creation of smart and automated systems.', 'Linear Actuator', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '195-autosave-v1', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:38:10', '2024-12-19 18:38:10', '', 195, 'http://localhost/?p=210', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(211, 1, '2024-12-19 18:43:49', '2024-12-19 18:43:49', 'The MQ-2 gas sensor is a versatile and widely used sensor for detecting various gases such as methane, propane, alcohol, and smoke. It is commonly used in projects related to air quality monitoring, safety systems, and gas leak detection. The sensor works by detecting changes in the resistance of its heating element in the presence of specific gases, providing an analog output that can be read by an Arduino. The sensor\'s sensitivity can be adjusted by calibrating it with different gases, making it highly adaptable for different applications.\n\nKey Features:\nOperating Voltage: Typically 5V, making it compatible with Arduino and other microcontrollers.\nDetection Gases: Methane (CH4), propane (C3H8), carbon monoxide (CO), smoke, alcohol, and more.\nSensitivity: Adjustable sensitivity, allowing fine-tuning for detecting specific gases.\nOutput Type: Analog output for continuous data and digital output for threshold detection.\nResponse Time: Quick response, typically within seconds after exposure to gases.\nApplications: Home safety systems, air quality monitoring, gas leak detection, environmental monitoring, and more.\nDurability: Reliable and long-lasting with proper calibration and maintenance.\nThe MQ-2 gas sensor is an affordable, easy-to-use component, perfect for building Arduino-based projects focused on detecting and monitoring gases in various environments.', 'Gas Sensor (MQ-2)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-autosave-v1', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:43:49', '2024-12-19 18:43:49', '', 193, 'http://localhost/?p=211', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(212, 1, '2024-12-19 18:49:55', '2024-12-19 18:49:55', 'The 0.96-inch OLED display is a compact and high-quality screen often used in Arduino projects to display text, graphics, and data. This display utilizes organic light-emitting diode (OLED) technology, which offers high contrast and bright colors without requiring a backlight, making it more energy-efficient compared to traditional LCD displays. The 0.96-inch size is ideal for small projects where space is limited. It typically uses an I2C interface, allowing easy communication with Arduino boards using just two data pins, simplifying wiring and minimizing pin usage.\n\nKey Features:\nDisplay Size: 0.96 inches, ideal for compact Arduino projects.\nResolution: 128x64 pixels, providing clear and sharp display of text and graphics.\nDisplay Type: OLED (Organic Light Emitting Diode), providing high contrast and bright colors with deep blacks.\nInterface: I2C communication (two data pins for easy connection).\nOperating Voltage: Typically 3.3V or 5V, compatible with most Arduino boards.\nLow Power Consumption: Does not require a backlight, making it energy-efficient.\nWide Viewing Angle: Offers excellent visibility from various angles.\nApplications: Displaying sensor data, time, status indicators, messages, and simple graphics in projects such as clocks, weather stations, and robotics.\n\nThe 0.96-inch OLED display is a popular choice for adding compact and clear visual output to Arduino projects, offering a simple and efficient solution for displaying a wide range of information.', 'OLED Display (0.96 inch)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '191-autosave-v1', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:49:55', '2024-12-19 18:49:55', '', 191, 'http://localhost/?p=212', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(213, 1, '2024-12-19 18:57:56', '2024-12-19 18:57:56', 'An IoT (Internet of Things) kit for Arduino is a comprehensive collection of components designed to help users build connected projects that communicate over the internet. With the increasing demand for smart devices and automation, this kit provides all the necessary hardware to get started with IoT applications. It typically includes sensors, actuators, communication modules, and other components that enable Arduino boards to collect data, process it, and send it to the cloud or other devices. The kit allows users to create projects such as remote monitoring systems, smart home automation, environmental monitoring, and much more.\n\nKey Features:\nComponents Included: Common components like  humidity sensors, motion detectors, relays, and Wi-Fi or Bluetooth modules (such as ESP8266, ESP32, or HC-05).\nConnectivity: Includes modules for Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, or GSM communication, enabling the Arduino board to connect to the internet or other devices.\nPlatform Compatibility: Compatible with Arduino IDE for easy programming and integration with cloud platforms like ThingSpeak, Blynk, or Adafruit IO.\nProject Variety: Ideal for creating smart home systems, weather stations, security systems, and other IoT applications.\nEase of Use: Detailed instructions and tutorials often come with the kit, making it beginner-friendly.\nExpandable: Can be expanded with additional sensors and modules for more complex projects.\n\nAn IoT kit for Arduino provides everything needed to build interactive, internet-connected projects, making it a great tool for learning and experimenting with IoT technologies.', 'IoT Kit', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '189-autosave-v1', '', '', '2024-12-19 18:57:56', '2024-12-19 18:57:56', '', 189, 'http://localhost/?p=213', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
